      "description": "Offering a pristine 2004 BMW M3, a definitive example of the E46 chassis. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies. The high-revving valvetrain remains quiet, with the double-VANOS system recently serviced for optimal cam timing. Power is delivered via a crisp ZF 6-speed manual transmission to a variable M differential lock. The subframe has been proactively reinforced, and the suspension geometry remains true with factory-spec bushings. Finished in iconic Laguna Seca Blue over Nappa leather, this vehicle exhibits zero cowl shake and a perfectly preserved undercarriage, representing a true collector-grade driving machine.",
